The South Loop is a dynamic mix of attractions and histories that the neighborhood tends to be seen as many different things to many different people. Consider the assorted areas that comprise the South Loop:

Much of its eastern edge is encompassed by the Museum Campus, an impressive collection of cultural treasures that includes the Field Museum, Adler Planetarium and Shedd Aquarium. This campus sits on scenic lakefront parklands that are an extension of Grant Park. With 319 acres of green space and recreational fields, Grant Park is known as "Chicago's front yard" to locals and also plays host to major city events such as Taste of Chicago, Chicago Blues Festival and Lollapalooza.

neighborhood_overview:
WRIGLEYVILLE
Wrigleyville is the lively little pocket in the Lakeview neighborhood that sits in the shadows of historic Wrigley Field, the second oldest stadium in baseball and home to the beloved Chicago Cubs. It has become a magnet for sports fans and young professionals alike, and particularly singles who hop from bar to bar along Clark, Addison and Sheffield Avenues. Rather tame by day, the neighborhood's souvenir shops and casual eateries are open but quiet. For late night entertainment, a boisterous after-hours crowd heads to Wrigleyville for everything from live music to sketch comedy. But if there's a day game or a night game letting out at "The Friendly Confines" then look out: the streets swell with the masses of fans looking to celebrate a Cubs win.

host_about:
Hi, we're Naomi and JJ. We've been avid Airbnb users for several years and since we loved Airbnb so much we decided to start hosting Airbnb stays in 2016.  

Naomi is a native Chicagoan (aka loyal Chicago Cubs' fan) who works in the tourism industry. While JJ, originally from Chicago's western suburbs, has been living in Wrigleyville and Boystown for over the last 15 years and is a whiz with our home automation (keypad king).  We also co-host our spaces with our retired parents Piya and Richard (who used to own two Pan Asian restaurants).  We have a ton of local tips about Chicago that we would love to share with you. In particular, we live to eat so have some great local eats suggestions for you.

Must see Chicago: Chicago Architecture River Cruise during the summer

Cheers!
Naomi and JJ

neighborhood_overview: Located in West Loop, this furnished rental invites you to explore the edges of downtown Chicago. From endless dining and bar options to art galleries and stylish shops, West Loop has emerged with so much to offer daily. During weekends, residents savor trips to the Chicago French Market and the vibrant strip of Randolph Street. The latter is known as “Restaurant Row” and is lined with some of the city’s best eateries. Fulton Market, one of the hippest and fastest-growing neighborhoods, is ideal for dinner and drinks. Union Station is only a 5 to 10 minute walk away.
host_about:
We’re Blueground, a global proptech company with several thousand move-in-ready apartments in a growing number of major cities around the world. With flexible terms and homes in vibrant, centrally based neighborhoods, you’ll feel at home and free to roam for as long as you want — a month, a year, or longer. 

Each apartment is thoughtfully designed with exclusive furnishings, fully equipped kitchens, and incredible amenities – making every day a five-star experience. From day one, you’ll enjoy high-speed Wi-Fi, premium linens, and smart home entertainment. Plus, access to pools, gyms, and outdoor spaces in select buildings.

Why stress over your apartment? We provide a hassle-free alternative — a consistent, quality guest experience that starts even before you arrive. Because we let you book our most up-to-date apartment listings online, confirm with a click, pay securely, and check in easily. 

Even better? You can enhance your stay with car rentals, grocery delivery, laundry services, and more through our special partnerships. 

During your stay
Upon arrival, you’ll either be greeted personally by a Blueground team member or given self-check-in instructions. The entire apartment is yours! You’ll enjoy reliable support via email, phone, and our Guest App, where you can request everything from a home cleaning to extra towels. 

We’ll share all details upon confirmation of your stay.

neighborhood_overview:
Why we love it
This cultural melting pot is known for its eclectic, artsy vibe. It’s one of the city’s up-and-coming hot spots, where you can uncover laidback taprooms, unique museums, old-school vintage shops, and tons of cool art — both in the galleries and on the streets.

Insider tips
Over the past century, West Town has seen waves of immigrants from all over the world. These global influences have shaped the neighborhood into the funky, creative enclave it is today. This is where you can find an Old-World pierogi joint, a nature-inspired brewery, and a contemporary omakase spot — all on the same street.

West Town encompasses the historic Ukrainian Village area, which brings tons of Eastern European heritage to the area. The Ukrainian National Museum, founded in 1952, houses an unparalleled collection of folk art, instruments, and artifacts that showcase Ukrainian history. neighborhood_overview: We are located in the heart of Humboldt Park--a vibrant, mainly Latino, family-based community.  One of Chicago largest parks is less than a block away with playgrounds, a lagoon, running trails, tennis courts, and a cafe during warmer months. There's a grocery store about eight blocks away, and lots of convenience stores for all of your snack and booze needs. host_about:
Hi! 
Thanks for visiting the profile page of FreeStand Home Solutions! 

We here at FHS, operate a corporate housing company, which means businesses and companies contract with us for housing, which typically averages 5-6 months.

We are NOT in the business of vacation renting. 

We simply list on these platforms because this is where businesses and companies come to search for housing.

Due to the nature of our business, we allow these same companies to "extend" their stay if they issue a request, 21 days prior to their lease expiration. 

If you are seeking long-term housing (30+ days), please submit an inquiry. Even if we do not have availability, we have additional temp housing companies we can recommend. We also have 50+ homes, so we are able to recommend an open location.

If you are seeking short-term housing (less than 30 days), we have a partner we work with, who may have availability. 

Please reach out to our office with additional questions, support and inquiries.
Pricing & calendar availability is accurate on FHS website only.

FreeStand Home Solutions

name: Palmer Treehouse - Bedroom 2
description:
Affordable in excellent Logan Sq location

The space
Cozy, beautiful, unique and rustic, this apartment overlooks and English style park in Logan Square. This apartment is not for everyone. Although it is beautiful, cozy, with comfortable beds, couches, etc - it is NOT a modern building...those with cat allergies, or who are very sensitive to the normal degree of dust in Victorian buildings will likely not be happy here. That said, we do try to keep things clean with regular dusting and an air purifier. A beautiful old greystone built in 1871, with an interesting history, and very characteristic of Chicago’s unique architectural trends of the era. If you have interest in older architecture, provided you do not have serious cat allergies, you will likely feel right at home. It's a great combo of vintage and new - especially on the 3rd floor, which is a little more updated. This listing includes the Palmer Oasis, which is one floor up. If you have a strong preferen
neighborhood_overview:
Logan sq has some of the best cuisine in Chicago, some would say the country! So if you are into eating like that, you will never have to leave the neighborhood.
It's also easy to rent bikes in Logan square, if you'd like to travel in a leisurely way around the neighborhood and city.
host_about:
I have been hosting on Airbnb for nearly a decade, and I love the opportunities to meet and connect with new people it brings. I travel frequently for work, but have enjoyed calling Chicago my home base for most of my life.  My roots in the neighborhood (Logan sq) go back generations; great grandparents on both sides (as well as one great-great grandmother!) lived and raised their families here, so the neighborhood history and its many changes and configurations are a personally fascinating subject to me. Sharing my favorite things about this uniquely down to earth and culturally diverse city is a passion of mine! 
I’m grateful that Airbnb allows me the privilege of connecting with other interesting/ interested travelers.

neighborhood_overview:
Back of the Yards is an industrial and residential neighborhood so named because it was near the former Union Stock Yards, which employed thousands of European immigrants in the early 20th century. Life in this neighborhood was explored in Upton Sinclair's 1906 novel The Jungle. The area was formerly part of the town of Lake until it was annexed by Chicago in 1889. In the late 19th and early 20th centuries, the area was occupied largely by Eastern European immigrants and their descendants, who were predominantly ethnic Bohemian, Moravian, and Slovak.[2]

In the 1930s the activist Saul Alinsky did community organizing in this area, as its people suffered during the Great Depression. This work led to his founding the Industrial Areas Foundation in 1940, which trained community organizers.[3]

neighborhood_overview: A vibrant blend of old and new, Sheridan Park is an intriguing neighborhood where Chicago's rich history and ethnic diversity intersect. This was a booming entertainment district for shopping and revelry in the 1920s and 1930s — though the area has witnessed multiple changes over time. Most recently, a renaissance has been underway in the Sheridan Park neighborhood and that formerly-faded glory is sparkling once again in the form of restored movie palaces and Art Deco beauties.
host_about: Life long Chicagoan excited to share the Northside experience with fellow travelers. The Brown Line train and Clark Street bus are the best ways to get around, especially with the Transit app.  Architectural boat tours downtown should be an everyone's list.

name: Bright Sunny Large Home EASY TRANSIT EVERYWHERE!
description:
A beautiful bright and sunny, three-story house with a large backyard (all photos are as of Feb 20, 2023).
The house is located on a beautiful and quiet tree-lined street with lots of free parking.
The large backyard includes a full swing set and trampoline, as well as a large functioning grill. Also includes many seasonal fruits and veggies that you can pick, including raspberries, blackberries, grapes, peaches, wild onions, etc. Great for long term rentals as well as long weekends...

The space
There are two living rooms: one main one on the first floor, and another TV/hang out area on the second floor. Both have futons which open up into beds.
If you’re traveling with kids, or babies, there is a fold-up arms-reach bassinet you are welcome to use, as well as a woven Moses basket bassinet. There is also a freestanding toddler mattress which you can set up in any room.
The two bedrooms on the second floor have black out curtains. The master
neighborhood_overview: Located close to EVERYTHING.  Just a few blocks away from the house is the beautiful Garfield Park with ducks and ponds, and the Garfield Park Conservatory (which is free) and is a must-see for kids and adults.  There are frequently events held there, and in the park.  For hockey and basketball fans, or if you're coming to Chicago for a concert, it's only about 5 min on the bus to the United Center.  It's a short 8 min ride to the Medical District, another short ride the other direction to historic Oak Park, which has many Frank Lloyd Wright masterpieces.  Though our generally quiet block is completely residential, it's certainly an urban/city feel.  We don't have bars and coffee shops and restaurants to walk to nearby, but all of that stuff is a very short drive.  There's a ton of artist lofts and urban farms and chickens and farmers markets and interesting things all around.

neighborhood_overview: This furnished apartment is located two miles west of downtown Chicago is the Illinois Medical District. This neighborhood is home to four major hospitals and two medical universities, in addition to more than 40 health care related facilities. The Illinois Medical District is exceptionally convenient, with plenty of places to shop for groceries and other necessities, including Costco. Nearby Addams-Medill Park is a great place to relax and play basketball or softball with friends on the weekend. The neighborhood is also home to the West Side Grounds, the former home of the Chicago Cubs and a draw for baseball and history lovers alike. The Illinois Medical District is served by Chicago's Blue and Pink lines.
host_about:
We’re Blueground, a global proptech company with several thousand move-in-ready apartments in a growing number of major cities around the world. With flexible terms and homes in vibrant, centrally based neighborhoods, you’ll feel at home and free to roam for as long as you want — a month, a year, or longer. 

Each apartment is thoughtfully designed with exclusive furnishings, fully equipped kitchens, and incredible amenities – making every day a five-star experience. From day one, you’ll enjoy high-speed Wi-Fi, premium linens, and smart home entertainment. Plus, access to pools, gyms, and outdoor spaces in select buildings.

Why stress over your apartment? We provide a hassle-free alternative — a consistent, quality guest experience that starts even before you arrive. Because we let you book our most up-to-date apartment listings online, confirm with a click, pay securely, and check in easily. 

Even better? You can enhance your stay with car rentals, grocery delivery, laundry services, and more through our special partnerships. 

During your stay
Upon arrival, you’ll either be greeted personally by a Blueground team member or given self-check-in instructions. The entire apartment is yours! You’ll enjoy reliable support via email, phone, and our Guest App, where you can request everything from a home cleaning to extra towels. 

We’ll share all details upon confirmation of your stay.

neighborhood_overview:
I've personally always loved Lincoln Square. The restaurants are incredible, the neighborhood is lively, and there are so many little shops to stop in and check out.

Attractions:
- For all you history buffs, check out the DANK Haus for a little history on the traditions, contributions of Germans and German Americans and German American language/culture! DANK stands for Deutsch Amerikanischer National Kongress which is a German American cultural center founded in 1959.
- Inside the Western Brown Line station is a remaining piece of the Berlin Wall that was donated to the city in 2008.
- Abraham Lincoln statue: A statue of Abraham Lincoln stands in the courtyard at Western and Lawrence which is really cool and after all, the neighborhood was named after the President!
- Lincoln Square Mural & Maipole: 3,000 square foot mural that features historical and iconic buildings and landscapes of Germany.

Places to eat:
- Elizabeth Restaurant: Michel

The space

neighborhood_overview: This furnished apartment is located in the Logan Square neighborhood. The area is one of Chicago’s trendiest and hippest neighborhoods, with a thriving arts and entertainment district on Milwaukee Avenue. Here, a strong local connection is evident, from active preservation groups to community gardens and a farmers market. Near the square, the boulevards become widened thoroughfares and are set apart by grassy, landscaped medians and tall, stately trees. The neighborhood has four in total and these link together to form Chicago's ‘Emerald Necklace’, an expansive system of interconnected parks and streetscapes. All along the parks, there are beautifully-restored mansions and majestic churches.
host_about:
We’re Blueground, a global proptech company with several thousand move-in-ready apartments in a growing number of major cities around the world. With flexible terms and homes in vibrant, centrally based neighborhoods, you’ll feel at home and free to roam for as long as you want — a month, a year, or longer. 

Each apartment is thoughtfully designed with exclusive furnishings, fully equipped kitchens, and incredible amenities – making every day a five-star experience. From day one, you’ll enjoy high-speed Wi-Fi, premium linens, and smart home entertainment. Plus, access to pools, gyms, and outdoor spaces in select buildings.

Why stress over your apartment? We provide a hassle-free alternative — a consistent, quality guest experience that starts even before you arrive. Because we let you book our most up-to-date apartment listings online, confirm with a click, pay securely, and check in easily. 

Even better? You can enhance your stay with car rentals, grocery delivery, laundry services, and more through our special partnerships. 

During your stay
Upon arrival, you’ll either be greeted personally by a Blueground team member or given self-check-in instructions. The entire apartment is yours! You’ll enjoy reliable support via email, phone, and our Guest App, where you can request everything from a home cleaning to extra towels. 

We’ll share all details upon confirmation of your stay.

neighborhood_overview:
A boom in trendy restaurants has put the Fulton Market District in Chicago's Near West Side neighborhood on the foodie map -- with long waits to prove it.
Au Cheval, a dimly lit bar and restaurant on Randolph Street, boasts what's widely touted as the city's best burger.
The double stack, covered in oozing cheese, has inspired some committed patrons to wait for the few coveted tables or bar seats for up to three hours.
"Top Chef" winner Stephanie Izard's tapas restaurant Girl & the Goat also earns rave reviews. Making a weekend reservation two months out can be a feat, so some people opt for its casual sister spot, Little Goat.
The elaborately prepared cocktails and imaginative molecular gastronomy of The Aviary cocktail lounge have turned it into a Fulton staple.
Chef-owner Grant Achatz, of renowned restaurant Alinea, has created ingredient-infused cocktails in space-age barware that require user participation -- like cracking an ice egg -- before enjoying.

It has two bedrooms with two new double beds, plus a small third bedroom with a single. The kitchen is all-new, outfitted for staying inside and cooking simple meals, and stocked with basic staples like coffee, tea, and snacks. The bathroom, fixtures and walk-in shower are all-new, too. For work, there's strong Wi-Fi and two dedicated work spaces. O
neighborhood_overview:
Logan Square is a thriving community of artists, musicians, and the indie spirit.
Beautiful Logan Boulevard anchors the neighborhood, lined with regal limestone homes, centered by the Illinois Centennial Monument, designed by the same architect who created the Lincoln Memorial in Washington D.C.

For nightlife, take your pick from trend-setting cocktail bars, under-the-radar venues with local bands, and burgeoning breweries and distilleries. Restaurants range from Michelin-rated spots, funky noodle shops, pizza and burger joints with cult followings, unexpected fusion concepts, and neighborhood favorite Lula Cafe, a pioneer of the farm-to-table movement. Hip coffee houses, boutiques, and a Sunday Farmers Market round out the Logan Square experience.

Just a few blocks away is the Logan Theatre, a vintage movie house opened in 1915, now rehabbed to include a cozy bar and lounge. "The Logan" screens everything from first-run films to late night cult classics to
host_about: I'm a freelance, work-at-home PR rep for Chicago non-profit theaters and performing arts organizations. My wife, Alicia, is a high school foreign language teacher (fluent in Spanish and French). We've lived and raised our two children in this wonderful old house since 2004. Now we're empty-nesters with a full garden apartment below our home, ready to welcome guests to Chicago.

neighborhood_overview:
If you chose to stay with us You're only a 9 minute walk from McCormick Place and a 4 minute walk from the Green Line Subway stop which gets you virtually everywhere in the City. You are also a short walk to a number of restaurants and attractions.

The South Loop is such a dynamic mix of attractions and histories that the neighborhood tends to be seen as many different things to many different people. Consider the assorted areas that comprise the South Loop:

Much of its eastern edge is encompassed by the Museum Campus, an impressive collection of cultural treasures that includes the Field Museum, Adler Planetarium and Shedd Aquarium. This campus sits on scenic lakefront parklands that are an extension of Grant Park. With 319 acres of green space and recreational fields, Grant Park is known as "Chicago's front yard" to locals and also plays host to major city events such as Taste of Chicago, Chicago Blues Festival and Lollapalooza.

The neighborhood is easily accessible to the rest of the city via the Blue Line or the 606. Bucktown living offers a laid back urban feel and is known to be one of the best areas in the city to live.
host_about:
We’re Blueground, a global proptech company with several thousand move-in-ready apartments in a growing number of major cities around the world. With flexible terms and homes in vibrant, centrally based neighborhoods, you’ll feel at home and free to roam for as long as you want — a month, a year, or longer. 

Each apartment is thoughtfully designed with exclusive furnishings, fully equipped kitchens, and incredible amenities – making every day a five-star experience. From day one, you’ll enjoy high-speed Wi-Fi, premium linens, and smart home entertainment. Plus, access to pools, gyms, and outdoor spaces in select buildings.

Why stress over your apartment? We provide a hassle-free alternative — a consistent, quality guest experience that starts even before you arrive. Because we let you book our most up-to-date apartment listings online, confirm with a click, pay securely, and check in easily. 

Even better? You can enhance your stay with car rentals, grocery delivery, laundry services, and more through our special partnerships. 

During your stay
Upon arrival, you’ll either be greeted personally by a Blueground team member or given self-check-in instructions. The entire apartment is yours! You’ll enjoy reliable support via email, phone, and our Guest App, where you can request everything from a home cleaning to extra towels. 

We’ll share all details upon confirmation of your stay.

neighborhood_overview: A vibrant blend of old and new, Sheridan Park is an intriguing neighborhood where Chicago's rich history and ethnic diversity intersect. This was a booming entertainment district for shopping and revelry in the 1920s and 1930s — though the area has witnessed multiple changes over time. Most recently, a renaissance has been underway in the Sheridan Park neighborhood and that formerly-faded glory is sparkling once again in the form of restored movie palaces and Art Deco beauties.

The Brown Line train and Clark Street bus are the best ways to get around, especially with the Transit app.  Architectural boat tours downtown should be an everyone's list.

neighborhood_overview:
We are located in the South Loop neighborhood of Chicago, which offers a variety of amenities and attractions. Here are some of the highlights:

Restaurants and bars: The South Loop is known for its diverse dining options, with a wide range of cuisines represented. Some popular restaurants in the area include Lou Malnati's Pizzeria, Yolk, and Eleven Eleven.

Shopping: The neighborhood is home to several retail destinations, including the Roosevelt Collection Shops, which features a mix of national and local retailers, as well as the historic Printer's Row neighborhood, known for its independent bookstores and literary history.

Entertainment: The South Loop is home to several cultural institutions, including the Field Museum of Natural History, the Adler Planetarium, and the Shedd Aquarium. The area also has several music venues and theaters, including the Chicago Symphony Orchestra and the Auditorium Theatre.

neighborhood_overview: This furnished rental is located in Streeterville, only a 5 minute walk from The Loop. One of the fastest-developing neighborhoods in Chicago, Streeterville extends out into Lake Michigan and attracts a blend of young professionals, students, and tourists. host_about:
We’re Blueground, a global proptech company with several thousand move-in-ready apartments in a growing number of major cities around the world. With flexible terms and homes in vibrant, centrally based neighborhoods, you’ll feel at home and free to roam for as long as you want — a month, a year, or longer. 

Each apartment is thoughtfully designed with exclusive furnishings, fully equipped kitchens, and incredible amenities – making every day a five-star experience. From day one, you’ll enjoy high-speed Wi-Fi, premium linens, and smart home entertainment. Plus, access to pools, gyms, and outdoor spaces in select buildings.

Why stress over your apartment? We provide a hassle-free alternative — a consistent, quality guest experience that starts even before you arrive. Because we let you book our most up-to-date apartment listings online, confirm with a click, pay securely, and check in easily. 

Even better? You can enhance your stay with car rentals, grocery delivery, laundry services, and more through our special partnerships. 

During your stay
Upon arrival, you’ll either be greeted personally by a Blueground team member or given self-check-in instructions. The entire apartment is yours! You’ll enjoy reliable support via email, phone, and our Guest App, where you can request everything from a home cleaning to extra towels. 

We’ll share all details upon confirmation of your stay.

description:
Have questions? Send an "Inquiry"! I'm flexible, as is this attractively-decorated 3BR apartment with 5 separate beds* + 2 optional infant beds. With free, easy street parking included, you'll find this home base in a quiet, residential area of NW Chicago comfy, private and accessible for both business or family.

*NOTE: The apartment has 5 BEDS, NOT 6! This counting error on the Airbnb platform can't be corrected. See details below and/or click on BR-2 photos to read explanatory captions.

The space
Pack light! Except for food and personal items, this house is equipped! Our fully furnished 3-bedroom, 1-bath garden apartment is peaceful and ready to be your temporary home. A roomy 1040 square feet with carpeted and tile floors, the space is allergy-free and stylishly furnished with your comfort in mind. It has separate access from a shared lobby with two upper level apartments. Although the apartment is situated on one level, from street parking t
neighborhood_overview: Our Galewood neighborhood is a diverse residential area with an Italian heritage.  Think of it as a hub, making access to multiple attractions easy -- Going east takes you through the Wicker Park/Bucktown creative centers into the Chicago Loop. Then directly south it's under 2 miles into the heart of Oak Park, known for unique shops, restaurants, theaters, tourism, and continuous events.  Further south is Midway Airport -- 11 miles from our house, as is O'Hare Airport 11 miles north. To the west, the suburbs offer their own temptations with Morton Arboretum and in the northwest, LEGOLAND Discovery Center.  Whatever way you chose to go, you can come home to rest, refresh, and relax in the very private space available to you here.  See my Guidebook for my family's recommendations for all our favorites nearby!
host_about:
Originally from the California Sierra Nevadas, I remember what it was like to be new to Chicago. When I arrived about sixteen years ago, lost — so many friendly people helped me find my way around until I learned to be at home in the city. Now retired,  it's my turn to be the helper for newcomers here on a visit.  Usually busy at home — a popular stopover with both friends and grandkids, I am known for incessant baking, and being perpetually prepared to share a hot pot of coffee with whomever stops by.

I am offering you the peace I enjoy and a comfortable, private stay here without interference. If you should need anything, however, do not hesitate to message me. Most likely I'm upstairs and available to answer any questions or concerns—or even just to chat! I want you to have a relaxed experience here, conveniently comfortable and at home away from home.

The space

Chicago is a city of neighborhoods, and Lincoln Square is a great place to begin exploring.

The apartment is o
neighborhood_overview: Lincoln Square is a vibrant, family-friendly neighborhood on the north side of Chicago that is full of activity year-round. You will find some of the best restaurants in Chicago from Michilen star chefs to deep dish pizza to Thai curries to South African inspired BBQ and anything and everything else in between. Lincoln Square can also serve as base camp to "Malt Row," duly named for the high number of breweries concentrated in one area and is deemed "Chicago's most diverse beer destination." Also, if you time your trip right, you'll find that Lincoln Square is host to some of the best neighborhood festivals in Chicago, including Square Roots, a weekend-long music festival hosted by the Old Town School of Folk Music. Finally, Lincoln Square is home to a number of great parks offering access to miles of running and bikes paths, playgrounds, and nature preserves; in fact, your apartment is steps from a miles-long walking/biking path through and along Chicago parks and riverbank.

host_about:
Born in a small town in Indiana, I have spent the majority of my life living in Chicago.  I own a small interior design firm and have spent the last 20 years trying to make things nice for myself and others. 

I was an early adopter of airbnb, joining the platform when I was renting a two bedroom flat and had a housemate move out unexpectedly.  I’ve spent my time as a host trying to figure out what an ideal airbnb experience is like…and I quickly realized how much pleasure it gives me to create an amazing place to share with travelers.  

Even though I am not hosting folks in my own home (I have a geriatric cat who no longer likes strangers) I want my guests to really experience an authentic slice of Chicago.  I hope that you will truly enjoy the spaces that I create and find each one to be a fun background player to your Chicago experience.

neighborhood_overview:
Boasting gorgeous boulevards and a constantly expanding selection of restaurants and bars, Logan Square is one of the city's trendiest neighborhoods, balancing family-friendly amenities with a thriving nightlife. Walk along Milwaukee Avenue and you'll find cocktail bars and gastropubs as well as dive bars and late night eateries, all packed with young crowds watching local bands or playing vintage arcade games. The variety of diversions present in Logan Square attracts record lovers, musicians, pinball wizards and dining aficionados to this scenic section of Chicago.

This Northwest Side neighborhood is rich in working class traditions and low-key charm. Its industrial character continues to evolve as longtime residents welcome the influx of artists, young professionals and new families drawn to the area's affordable homes, easy access to downtown and multicultural heritage.

East Garfield Park is the next great place to live in Chicago - kind of like where the west Loop and United Center neighborhoods were 5 years ago. The immediate area surrounding 637 W Cornelia Ave is primarily residential with tree-lined streets, single-family homes, and multi-unit apartment buildings. With flexible terms and homes in vibrant, centrally based neighborhoods, you’ll feel at home and free to roam for as long as you want — a month, a year, or longer. 

Each apartment is thoughtfully designed with exclusive furnishings, fully equipped kitchens, and incredible amenities – making every day a five-star experience. River North is perhaps the most stylish section of Chicago, and that’s no small accomplishment. The thoroughly-urban neighborhood features a truly staggering array of art galleries and a cutting edge design district, making it a magnet for folks who are passionate about the visual arts.

The neighborhood is known for its vibrant nightlife, bustling shopping districts, excellent dining options, and proximity to Wrigley Field, home of the Chicago Cubs. It is also home to several music venues, including the Metro and the Vic Theatre, which attract big-name acts and up-and-coming artists alike.

Lakeview is also home to numerous parks, including Lincoln Park, which is one of the largest parks in the city and features a zoo, a conservatory, and miles of walking and biking paths. Additionally, the neighborhood boasts several excellent schools, including Nettelhorst Elementary School, which is known for its strong academic program.

neighborhood_overview:
In Old Town Chicago you’ll find historic charm in the form of brick alleyways, Victorian-era buildings, family-owned restaurants and an eclectic atmosphere. In addition to being home to St. Michael’s Church, one of only buildings that survived the Great Chicago Fire, it’s also where many great comedians (like Bill Murray) got their start at The Second City comedy club. The distinctive architecture aside, this historic neighborhood is a classic Chicago landmark with no shortage of dining, shopping and entertainment.

If you have time to kill then you’ll be happy to know these famous attractions are within a mile of your luxury suite:

360 Chicago

description:
Visiting Chicago? Stay in true Windy City style by joining us in our historic 3-flat in the Lakeview neighborhood on Chicago's North Side within walking distance of Wrigley Field and the popular Southport Corridor of restaurants, bars and shops.

The space
You are staying in a historic building constructed in 1893 at the time of the World's Columbian Exposition held in Chicago. We completed a complete gut rehabilitation of the property in 2007 but preserved the period look and feel of the building with state of the art electrical, plumbing, HVAC, internet and sound systems. This private Bedroom and private Bathroom across the hall are located on the 3rd floor of our historic home. Both bedroom and bathroom have privacy latches. The bedroom has an integrated USB port in the outlet near the bed so there is no need for a converter. You have access to a shared free laundry and our fully equipped Kitchen with refrigerator, stove, cooktop, microwaves, toaster oven, c
neighborhood_overview: Lakeview is a historic part of Chicago, having developed outside the city limits and being annexed to the city in the late 1800's. Our immediate neighborhood was developed on land originally owned by Graceland Cemetery, which is our neighbor to the East. It is a worthwhile walking trip and contains the graves of many of Chicago's founding fathers and commercial elite. Immediately South of us is Southport Avenue which contains a diverse group of restaurants, bars, shops, the Mercury live theater and The Music Box cinema theater. It is a pleasant walk on your way to or from our other historic landmark - Wrigley Field - home of the Chicago Cubs baseball club. We are also walking distance to the Black Ensemble Theater to our North which produces live musical shows centered on diverse musicians. We are a longer walk to Lincoln Avenue and the historic Old Town School of Folk Music with its regular classes and concert venues. Further East on Broadway is the classic Chicago speakeasy The Green
host_about: We've lived in our historic 1893 Chicago three-flat since 1979, raised our children here and now offer our Garden level and bedroom/bathrooms to AirBNB guests after our own highly successful AirBNB experiences in New York, London, Ireland, Ontario, Venice, Barcelona, Lisbon and Madrid.  My wife Barbara and I love to travel and love to share the Chicago experience with people around the world.  Come join us.

neighborhood_overview: We want to under promise and over deliver.  So we want to be clear that this property is on Chicago's West side in an amazing multicultural and ethnically diverse neighborhood.  It is, for sure in the inner city.  It's full of grime and glory.  You can't walk to a coffee shop but you can make eye contact and chit chat with a total stranger. Not many places in a big city where that happens anymore.
host_about: Our quality of life depends on how well we deal with adversity!  Feel positive. Live positive.  I grew up in a small coastal town in Maine.  When I turned 19 I realized that I was a closet wanderer.  So I hit the road and covered much of the U.S. and all of Europe.  I taught skiing in the Rockies and rode my BMW R65-LS from coast to coast.  When I was in Europe I was amazed at how willing people were to open their homes to a total stranger.  I had one of my best experiences living with a family in Romania in the Carpathian Mountains.  Amazing!  I feel this is the best way possible to travel.  It's part of why I love Air B&B.  Hotel shmotel!  Live the life of the area.  That's an experience.  Now my wandering days are over.  I'm rooted in one of the coolest communities I know.  Rich with art and spirit. I have two amazing girls that help me garden, can, collect eggs and milk.  My partner is a fellow East Coast boy, world class jazz pianist and my right hand man. I also tour with an ABBA tribute band as well as a Pink Floyd tribute band but don't hold that against me.  I hope you like it here half as much as we do!!

host_about:
Welcome to Lang House Chicago, an architectural gem available for your  Chicago vacation.   Lang House Chicago is a professionally managed vacation rental in the Rogers Park neighborhood.  Chicago is all about neighborhoods, architecture and history.  Lang House Chicago has it all; located right on Sheridan Road just 1 block from Lake Michigan, Lang House is a Four Square Prairie Style home designed by Edgar Newman and built in 1919.  The home is beautifully preserved and elegantly appointed.  

My team includes professional property managers and hospitality staff.  We  work for a company that restores and manages historically significant homes.  Lang House Chicago is a home that reflects the pride and love of many of us on the management team.  We are happy to be your hosts! 

My name is Carmen and I have lived in Chicago for 11 years, having moved around the country throughout my life, and settling here with my family.  It had always been my dream to live in Chicago due to the rich architecture,  which is unlike that of any other city in the world.  I have grown to love the lake and the history of this city.      

Please send a message if you have any questions about the home or the neighborhood.  I can also help you with recommendations for local restaurants and must-see attractions in Chicago.

neighborhood_overview: Chicago West Loop-Fulton is a vibrant neighborhood located in the heart of Chicago, Illinois. Known for its mix of modern and historic architecture, the area features a plethora of trendy restaurants, chic boutiques, and art galleries. The neighborhood is home to several major attractions, including the United Center, home of the Chicago Bulls and Chicago Blackhawks, as well as the Oprah Winfrey Network headquarters. Downtown by subway or bus is about 30 minutes from The Polished Knob.

Established in the late 1800s, the community of Edgewater was conceived as an arcadian retreat to the hustle and grim of Chicago back in the day. Large, child friendly, updated apartment on the border of Logan Square and Bucktown neighborhoods in Chicago. Although the home is on a quiet street, it is within a half mile walk of many businesses/activities: live music, a comedy venue, bowling, and a multitude of restaurants, bars, gym and retail establishments.

The location is also close to public transportation: the Blue Line 'El' Train and bus system. Of course, rideshare services (Uber) are plentiful and there is onsite parking.

The space
The rooms have comfy tempur-pedic beds, space heaters and fans. There are also pack n play, diaper gene, high chair and baby tub. The wall plugs are covered to keep away curious fingers.

Guest access
The house is a 2 flat and you have access to 2 floors, garage and laundry.

Other things to note
Also, there is a smart TV in the living room and 2 rooms have Roku TVs. They are all connected to the apartment's powerfu
neighborhood_overview:
Although the house is on a quiet, tree-lined street, the neighborhood is vibrant.

The 'El' is just a couple blocks away. It's a Blue Line stop that goes out to O'Hare airport or heads directly downtown where there are transfers available to the other trains that can take you all over the city.

It's difficult to list all of the interesting proprietors within just a half mile of the house. There are many restaurants (including Japanese, Mexican, Cuban, Italian, breakfast diners, fast food, etc), many bars (including breweries, taprooms, dives, even an arcade bar), groceries, bowling, gym and coffee houses. Also, just around the corner is a stand-up comedy joint and a live music venue.

name: Just Passing Through Gold Coast One Bedroom #407
description:
Cozy one bedroom apartment in vintage renovated courtyard building located in Chicago's Gold Coast area. Close to everything--restaurants, shopping, downtown, public transportation. Building has secure entry with overnight security.

The space
This is a perfect apartment and location for a short-term stay. The apartment has a queen size bed and can accommodate 1 or 2 people. The building is located in a residential neighborhood, but is a short walk or commute to downtown Chicago. It's steps to several grocery stores, countless restaurants and shops. Walk to Michigan Avenue or the lakefront.

host_about: I'm a former university administrator who saw the need for short-term housing. More than 25 years ago I started a business providing furnished, short-term accommodations. My husband and I enjoy going to billiards tournaments, bull riding competitions, traveling and hanging out with our 4 grandkids.

neighborhood_overview:
Chicago is not only 200 diverse neighborhoods, 552 parks, 5000 boats in the harbor, 5000 annual music performances, 200 art galleries, 200 theaters, 40 annual film festivals, 2 major league baseball teams, 100 floors in the Willis Tower, 23 Michelin-Starred restaurants and 15 miles of public beaches; it's also the 4th largest municipal GDP in the world, with 10 million Chicagoland residents, 1 million flight departures and 40 million visitors per year.
Scroll down to my Guidebook for personal picks and experiment the adrenaline of our city from a quiet corner, at one of the most representative African American suburbs, with locals whose daily train ride offers them someone to share their stories with. This urban mixture of beautiful street murals and police news, electronic music mixed with men dancing in bus stops, mothers who bring their children to preschool mixed with basketball players, in short, the daily story of millions in Chicago's South Side, a side with a heritage not
host_about: Passionate about this city, I love welcoming you to my home. Former hospitality worker and teacher whose motivations include music, languages, cycling and traveling. I lived abroad, taught to thousands of international students, received grants and degrees by universities and foundations in United Kingdom and United States. While born and raised in Uruguay (as per the New York Times: the 'Switzerland' of Latin America for most of the country's history) we ran a small hotel in Punta del Este: a seaside city referred by Travel+Leisure and Newsweek as "the St-Tropez of South America", "the Hamptons of Latin America" or "South America's Monaco". My family was among the visionaries who settled in Punta del Este before it became internationally known as a jet set and tourist destination, built, and ran their hotel during sixty years. They originally emigrated to Uruguay from Italy, Turkey and Lithuania (escaped antisemitism, systemic racism, and poverty in Europe). As a teenager, I participated in my local 'Interact Club' or the youth division for Rotary International; fast forward twenty years as U.S. permanent resident, I now advocate for Airbnb Open Homes on humanitarian relief to refugees and Airbnb Project Lighthouse to fight social stigmata, and against discrimination.

Pilsen is a neighborhood located on the Lower West Side of Chicago, Illinois. It is known for its vibrant Mexican-American culture and rich history. The neighborhood is home too many colorful murals and street art, which reflect the community's cultural heritage.

Pilsen is also a popular destination for art lovers, as it boasts several galleries and artist studios. The neighborhood is also home to a number of delicious Mexican restaurants, taquerias and cafes, making it a great place to experience authentic Mexican cuisine.

Pilsen is also known for its rich architecture, including historic grey stone buildings and colorful Victorian homes. The area is also known for being close to downtown and public transportation, making it a popular choice for young professionals and students.

She is born and raised in the amazing neighborhood Pilsen this is where we have chose to plant our flag as a family.  Pilsen is filled with so much culture from arts, music and amazing food.  In the summer you can definitely catch us at the many music and food fest that Pilsen and surrounding neighborhoods have.  You can catch us at the park playing with our daughter eating an “Elote” (Corn on stick) or “Paleta” (Mexican Popsicle) just enjoying the Chicago weather.

We became homeowners in 2018 and we now are excited to share what we have built with our guests.  When investing In Pilsen the buildings are old need allot of work, but have amazing character.  We have spent the last year making our property perfect while preserving the character.  We love to travel so we understand how important room accommodations are.  So we hope to make you as comfortable as possible on your visit to Pilsen and Chicago.  We love help so if there is anything you need please don’t hesitate to ask.  We look forward to having you as a guest in Pilsen and beautiful city of Chicago.

The South Loop is such a dynamic mix of attractions and histories that the neighborhood tends to be seen as many different things to many different people. host_about:
Hi, we're Bob and Liz Biddle, long time Chicagoans and your hosts. We started At Home Inn Chicago in 2000 as a reservation service for bed and breakfasts in Chicago, and have since evolved into one of the city's most-respected sources for vacation rentals, corporate housing, and weekend getaways. 

We provide fully furnished vacation rentals and corporate housing throughout the city in or near Old Town and Lincoln Park.

We are here to answer all of your questions about Chicago, whether you need a restaurant recommendation, public transit tips, or insider tips on how to experience the Chicago that locals know and love. 

We love this city, especially getting ribs at Twin Anchors in Old Town before a show at Second City.  Topo Gigio is a great local Italian Restaurant and The Gemini Bistro is an excellent choice for fine dining. And Velvet Taco, casual with its own unique style on Lincoln is fabulous!

The free concerts at Pritzker Pavilion in Millenium Park can't be matched by any city in the world. 

We'd love to help you experience all of this with us and so much more!

neighborhood_overview: Located in West Loop, this furnished rental invites you to explore the edges of downtown Chicago. From endless dining and bar options to art galleries and stylish shops, West Loop has emerged with so much to offer daily. During weekends, residents savor trips to the Chicago French Market and the vibrant strip of Randolph Street. The latter is known as “Restaurant Row” and is lined with some of the city’s best eateries. Fulton Market, one of the hippest and fastest-growing neighborhoods, is ideal for dinner and drinks. Union Station is only a 5 to 10 minute walk away.
host_about:
We’re Blueground, a global proptech company with several thousand move-in-ready apartments in a growing number of major cities around the world. With flexible terms and homes in vibrant, centrally based neighborhoods, you’ll feel at home and free to roam for as long as you want — a month, a year, or longer. 

Each apartment is thoughtfully designed with exclusive furnishings, fully equipped kitchens, and incredible amenities – making every day a five-star experience. From day one, you’ll enjoy high-speed Wi-Fi, premium linens, and smart home entertainment. Plus, access to pools, gyms, and outdoor spaces in select buildings.

Why stress over your apartment? We provide a hassle-free alternative — a consistent, quality guest experience that starts even before you arrive. Because we let you book our most up-to-date apartment listings online, confirm with a click, pay securely, and check in easily. 

Even better? You can enhance your stay with car rentals, grocery delivery, laundry services, and more through our special partnerships. 

During your stay
Upon arrival, you’ll either be greeted personally by a Blueground team member or given self-check-in instructions. The entire apartment is yours! You’ll enjoy reliable support via email, phone, and our Guest App, where you can request everything from a home cleaning to extra towels. 

We’ll share all details upon confirmation of your stay.

host_about:
Love Travelers,  traveling and everything in between.  Born and raised in Chicago, we became avid travellers and barter enthusiasts. With over 20 years of travelling we could easily write our own book on travelling on a budget.  We PRIDE ourselves on the deals we obtain.  A week in Ireland, rental of two 3 bedroom entire homes for $45! FOUR Chicago Bull playoff games during the Michael Jordan Era included 4th row floor seats, box seats...$100 total!  Travelled europe thru 15 countries for $500 including accommodations and food...for a 3 month period!  And this was BEFORE Airbnb. We can go on.  We are geeked when we find a deal and become just plain silly with happiness at an unbelievable deal.  Even upon confirmation, our website for our guests are filled with free and things to do for CRAZY CHEAP.  'Spend like a spencer, but live like a king!'  

We feel everyone should open their minds to new things, cultural experiences and diversity.  Only then can you understand people thru their eyes and not some narrow minded media coverage.  By letting their experience be your experience will help you better understand people in a true and raw sense.  That's why we simply love Airbnb.  It places you in parts of the world where you probably wouldn't have gone but always wanted to go to get that 'local' feel with a local and trusted host.   

Since we don't travel as much as I used to....Let your experience be our experience!

We look forward to meeting you.

host_about:
Henrik & I  are entrepreneurs who mostly work from home. We have businesses that allow us to travel almost anywhere! Our motto is, as long as a place has WIFI, we can work from there! So we usually go there :)

Henrik's from Oslo Norway, since he moved to Chicago, he's used Airbnb to keep his home there while he lives with me in Chicago! When we are in Norway or elsewhere in the world, we open up 1350 to beautiful people like yourself.

Because we work from home we have made 1350 our shrine. We love 1350 so much. Whenever a new person comes into our home, they feel a sense of peace and expansion. We have spent many years pouring our love and energy into 1350. Because we travel often to Norway for long periods of time, we figured why not share our place with folks who will feel the love there. 

When we are home in Chicago, we like to host and entertain people. Katelyn loves to cook and make yummy cocktails for her friends & family while Henrik likes to dance and make people laugh. If we are not at home, you probably will find us at our favorite BYOB sushi joints or for a burger and mussels at Tuamns Tap. We are a laid back couple who loves to connect with humans making an impact in the world.

neighborhood_overview:
River North is perhaps the most stylish section of Chicago, and that’s no small accomplishment. The thoroughly-urban neighborhood features a truly staggering array of art galleries and a cutting edge design district, making it a magnet for folks who are passionate about the visual arts.

The dining and nightlife scenes are just as diverse and exquisite as the local arts community, with a massive assortment of restaurants, bars, and clubs catering to every taste.

The landscape is treasure trove of architecture, featuring many well-preserved historic buildings well over a century old alongside midcentury masterpieces and ultra-modern skyscrapers. The Magnificent Mile runs along the east side of the neighborhood, and Downtown is right across the river. Folks pay a premium to live here, but most agree it’s well worth the hefty price tag.

neighborhood_overview: Just 5 miles from downtown, Roscoe Village is a charming, laidback “village within the city” filled with casual taverns, independent shops, and cute cafes that spill out onto the sidewalks during the warm weather months. This cozy little pocket is an eclectic mix of unique boutiques, classic frame and brick homes, and locally owned eateries. It’s a wonderfully welcoming and quirky place. neighborhood_overview:
Streeterville is a neighborhood in the Near North Side community area of Chicago, north of the Chicago River. It is bounded by the river on the south, the Magnificent Mile portion of Michigan Avenue to the west, and Lake Michigan to the east. The City of Chicago only recognizes a small portion of this region as Streeterville. Thus, it can be described as the Magnificent Mile plus all land east of it.

Streeterville includes some of Chicago's tallest skyscrapers, such as the John Hancock Center, and upscale stores, hotels, and restaurants. The east side of Streeterville is Navy Pier, the most visited attraction in Chicago, and the John Hancock Observatory, the eighth-most visited attraction in Chicago.

The Northwestern University Feinberg School of Medicine is on the Chicago campus and is adjacent to several closely affiliated hospitals, including Northwestern Memorial Hospital, the Ann & Robert H. Lurie Children's Hospital of Chicago, the Prentice Women's Hospital

neighborhood_overview:
Back of the Yards is an industrial and residential neighborhood so named because it was near the former Union Stock Yards, which employed thousands of European immigrants in the early 20th century. Life in this neighborhood was explored in Upton Sinclair's 1906 novel The Jungle. The area was formerly part of the town of Lake until it was annexed by Chicago in 1889. In the late 19th and early 20th centuries, the area was occupied largely by Eastern European immigrants and their descendants, who were predominantly ethnic Bohemian, Moravian, and Slovak.[2]

In the 1930s the activist Saul Alinsky did community organizing in this area, as its people suffered during the Great Depression. This work led to his founding the Industrial Areas Foundation in 1940, which trained community organizers.[3]

neighborhood_overview: Lovely, friendly, with kids and dogs and old people (and some new families too). It's not a trendy/hip neighborhood (just yet) so we lack a lot of walking to restaurants and marketing for shopping. However there are a few nice places that you can walk, and which I will recommend. There are loads of grocery stores about a mile away in every direction. We especially like the 24 hour hamburger stand (Suzie's) in the summer time, for shakes and grilled goodies. A greasy spoon for breakfast is the Golden Nugget. New to the hood is the amazing Old Irving Brewing brewpub which many guests frequent several times per week because it's so good and so close. Other stuff: I prefer Sarapino's or Lou Malnati's for pizza, #1 Chop Suey or Chen's Garden for Chinese, and PotBelly or Jimmy Johns for sandwiches. We have a couple Starbucks as well as two awesome independent coffee shops (Cafe Urbano and Coffee Roasters). All fairly close by. We go to mass at St Eds across the street. There are at least six
host_about:
I am a divorced father of four. That's my three kids in the scooter sidecar with me when they were young. They recently moved to Reading, PA and I visit them every few weeks. My oldest daughter is all grown up in Texas with my grandson. 
I worked for Apple for 6 years. I currently consult with companies about technology/internet/social media/marketing/branding. I work at AbbVie as a contractor for the last two years. 
We own the entire building and I work and live (some of the time) on the third floor with tenants on first floor. We use AirBnB for the Garden Apartment (totally private); the second floor is a hostel style AirBnB; and upstairs on the 3rd floor we have up to two bedrooms that are available when I don’t have my kids in town.
I enjoy going on bike rides to the beach with my kids, and my girlfriend and her kids. I love to read and I am a tech geek. I am a coffee OR tea drinker and after drinking both black for almost forty years, I have started using cream in them — a habit I picked up in Nairobi, Kenya a couple years ago when I was doing some missionary work (plus my girlfriend uses cream and so I have no choice). 
If I had to pick some things I can't live without: my girlfriend (and her boys); my kids; my technology; my morning coffee; my fellowship; and my friends. And I love to watch movies. Old. New. Comedy. Mystery. Action. It doesn't matter. I like them all. 
I enjoy working out — lifting weights, rowing machine, Pilates, and riding a bike; plus I am a life-long swimmer. I also recently started playing hockey! At my age (over 50!). Crazy. 
We have been hosting guests for over five years now. We have over 250 reviews 98% are 5 star. We are a SuperHost. We love this. And we are really good at it.
I am a pretty laid back guy. I like things to be neat and tidy, but it's hard to do without motivation. AirBnB has been the motivation to get our place all tricked out and we are very proud of it. We hope you will enjoy staying here. All of our units are in a great neighborhood—in a great city. We have lots of suggestions for fun stuff to do, not the typical touristy stuff, but cool Chicago things that Chicagoans like to do/see.

neighborhood_overview:
Why we love it
Lakeview’s laidback atmosphere and picture-perfect shoreline make it a favorite hang out among locals. And spots like lively Wrigleyville and the Belmont Theater District make it a major entertainment hub, too.

Insider tips
Anchored by a beautiful stretch of shoreline to the east, Lakeview melds several distinct areas — East Lakeview, Central Lakeview, Boystown, and Wrigleyville. Each spot has its own unique character, but they’re all pulled together by Lakeview’s casual, welcoming feel.

Hit the bustling shopping districts along Broadway in East Lakeview, along Belmont near Boystown, and the bustling Southport Corridor for local boutiques, record shops, and vintage treasure hunting. neighborhood_overview: Printers Row is “pocket” neighborhood just minutes from the Chicago Loop. After the Great Chicago Fire of 1871, the area became the Midwest hub of the printing industry with historically significant buildings designed by legendary architects like Daniel Burnham, William Holabird and William Le Baron Jenney. Today, many of those historic buildings remain but the quiet, tree lined streets are now largely residential. Of course, it continues to be a draw for fans of Chicago architecture.

We here at FHS, operate a corporate housing company, which means businesses and companies contract with us for housing, which typically averages 5-6 months.

neighborhood_overview:
The house is in east Old Town- the best neighborhood in Chicago for both families or if you are looking to have fun.

Old Town is an active and eclectic neighborhood with a diverse and unique history. Originating as a home and trade center for Native American nations, including Potawatomi, Miami and Illinois, the area was founded in the 1850s by German settlers. Immigrants began to farm potatoes, celery and cabbage, which is where Old Town inherited its nickname as “The Cabbage Patch” in the early 1900s.

The German settlers also built St. Michael’s Church, the oldest Victorian building in the neighborhood, and one of the only buildings that survived the Great Chicago Fire. In fact, many of the streets in the Old Town neighborhood were constructed before the Fire and were not part of the Chicago street grid built after the devastating event.

Beginning in the 1920s, the neighborhood became a center of art and culture. Artists like Sol Kogen and Edgar Mill

The South Loop is such a dynamic mix of attractions and histories that the neighborhood tends to be seen as many different things to many different people. Consider the assorted areas that comprise the South Loop:

Much of its eastern edge is encompassed by the Museum Campus, an impressive collection of cultural treasures that includes the Field Museum, Adler Planetarium and Shedd Aquarium. This campus sits on scenic lakefront parklands that are an extension of Grant Park. With 319 acres of green space and recreational fields, Grant Park is known as "Chicago's front yard" to locals and also plays host to major city events such as Taste of Chicago, Chicago Blues Festival and Lollapalooza.

This campus sits on scenic lakefront parklands that are an extension of Grant Park. host_about:
I love to travel and explore different places and countries. I have been to most of the European countries. Ireland is my favorite and have a thatched cottage in County Kerry that has been a labor of love. Animals are a big passion of mine and I have 4 dogs. They are all rescue dogs and 2 of them are from Ireland. I support Young at Heart which is a No Kill senior animal rescue. My family is a big part of my life. I have a a son who has been a big part of working on the cottage since he was 7. Blessed to come from a very loving family. I have 3 sisters and 1 brother. My beautiful mother Mary Rose who is 92 works 5 days a week for our 63 year old family business. 
I was a member of the Guardsmen Drum and Bugle Corps from Schaumburg Il. I marched for 10 years and directed and taught this group for 17 (Website hidden by Airbnb) younger brother and sister also marched in the group. My parents and sisters were involved in some way or another. In 2012 the Harty Family was inducted in to the Heartland Drum Corps Association Hall of Fame. The Guardsmen made the DCI World Championship Finals 4 times. The indoor winter colorguard made the WGI World finals 10 times and won a Bronze medal in 1981. I was one of the founders of the WGI organization. 
We love Chicago and County Kerry. They are 2 amazing places to live and visit!

neighborhood_overview: Uptown is about 6 miles north of downtown Chicago. With Lake Michigan as its eastern boundary, Uptown has some of the city’s top beaches. We’re Blueground, a global proptech company with several thousand move-in-ready apartments in a growing number of major cities around the world. With flexible terms and homes in vibrant, centrally based neighborhoods, you’ll feel at home and free to roam for as long as you want — a month, a year, or longer.

From day one, you’ll enjoy high-speed Wi-Fi, premium linens, and smart home entertainment. Plus, access to pools, gyms, and outdoor spaces in select buildings.

Why stress over your apartment? We provide a hassle-free alternative — a consistent, quality guest experience that starts even before you arrive. Because we let you book our most up-to-date apartment listings online, confirm with a click, pay securely, and check in easily.

host_about:
2022:  Due to the shared nature of our property,  we are only taking guests who are vaccinated against covid.  

We are no longer refunding in full for guests who book with us and we turn away for not having their vaccination card or valid proof of a qualified medical exemption.  We are unable to continue paying for other people's mistakes :(  

When this happens, our ad was taken down and not able to be booked by other people.  

In the event you booked and made a mistake and catch it within an hour, go up to your itinerary and hit cancel.  It will say you get no refund.  Assuming this is done within the first hour of booking, we will refund you in full from our end.   If it's been more than an hour, any refund will be on a case by case basis based on how soon the reservation is.    

______________________________


Hello!  This is Joe, Alex, and Charlie.  If you stay here we will be your hosts while here in Chicago.   You may also hear from Bilal, Thomas, or Drew as they assist us sometimes.  Do NOT go to them on site and ask Airbnb related stuff as they are not paid for that.  

We are Airbnb Superhosts not because we have a 5 star luxury property, but because we just about always deliver on what we offer.  The best value in Chicago at this price point doing mostly shared, hostel-style accommodations.  


Please read through our entire ad and offering before asking questions or requesting a stay.  If after that you still have questions feel free to ask.  If you just want to book after reading, I'm positive we will deliver a great stay.   

Its not personal, but if you ask us questions located in our ad, we're probably going to redirect you there. A requirement on Airbnb is for a guest to read and abide by a hosts house rules and ad which is impossible if you dont  read them.  This is our way of gently helping people learn to use the platform the right way and prevent issues.  

99% of guest issues are related to the property not matching the guests expectations.  If the host is doing their job right, their ad should paint a pretty clear picture of what life is like at their place.



All of our listings include desks, gigabit internet to share, a full array of breakfast items including bacon, eggs, milk, orange juice, coffee, cereal, tea, oatmeal, at least 2x of fruit, 2x of vegi, cheese,  bread and jam, and we also take requests for other items that you may enjoy like yogurt, almond milk, or other vegis and fruits we dont already have.  We also often cook for guests and like filling the cookie jar with delicious baked goods throughout the month.  

We have been hosting here for 10 years and absolutely love it.  If youd like to share a drink or toke some of the shrubbery with me, let me know and I may be able to make that happen =)  We are 420 friendly in the backyard.  

We love Airbnb, Chicago, and our guests.   If privacy and being downtown are not important to you, you'll be hard pressed to find a better Airbnb experience in Chicago at this price point and if you do, we'll probably price match. 

NO room may have more than 2 adults.  The system has no way of differentiating adults from kids so this is the only way we can accommodate those with kids.  If you book with three adults, we will not be able to host the third in the same room.  

We all look forwarding to meeting those of you who book with us!

2022:  Due to the shared nature of our property,  we are only taking guests who are vaccinated against covid.

If it's been more than an hour, any refund will be on a case by case basis based on how soon the reservation is.    

______________________________


Hello!  This is Joe, Alex, and Charlie.  If you stay here we will be your hosts while here in Chicago.   You may also hear from Bilal, Thomas, or Drew as they assist us sometimes.  Do NOT go to them on site and ask Airbnb related stuff as they are not paid for that.  

We are Airbnb Superhosts not because we have a 5 star luxury property, but because we just about always deliver on what we offer.  The best value in Chicago at this price point doing mostly shared, hostel-style accommodations.  


Please read through our entire ad and offering before asking questions or requesting a stay.  If after that you still have questions feel free to ask.  If you just want to book after reading, I'm positive we will deliver a great stay.   

Its not personal, but if you ask us questions located in our ad, we're probably going to redirect you there. A requirement on Airbnb is for a guest to read and abide by a hosts house rules and ad which is impossible if you dont  read them.  This is our way of gently helping people learn to use the platform the right way and prevent issues.  

99% of guest issues are related to the property not matching the guests expectations.  If the host is doing their job right, their ad should paint a pretty clear picture of what life is like at their place.



All of our listings include desks, gigabit internet to share, a full array of breakfast items including bacon, eggs, milk, orange juice, coffee, cereal, tea, oatmeal, at least 2x of fruit, 2x of vegi, cheese,  bread and jam, and we also take requests for other items that you may enjoy like yogurt, almond milk, or other vegis and fruits we dont already have.  We also often cook for guests and like filling the cookie jar with delicious baked goods throughout the month.  

We have been hosting here for 10 years and absolutely love it.  If youd like to share a drink or toke some of the shrubbery with me, let me know and I may be able to make that happen =)  We are 420 friendly in the backyard.  

We love Airbnb, Chicago, and our guests.   If privacy and being downtown are not important to you, you'll be hard pressed to find a better Airbnb experience in Chicago at this price point and if you do, we'll probably price match. 

NO room may have more than 2 adults.  The system has no way of differentiating adults from kids so this is the only way we can accommodate those with kids.  If you book with three adults, we will not be able to host the third in the same room.  

We all look forwarding to meeting those of you who book with us!

neighborhood_overview:
Gold Coast / Streeterville are neighborhoods in the Near North Side community area of Chicago, north of the Chicago River. It is bounded by the river on the south, the Magnificent Mile portion of Michigan Avenue to the west, and Lake Michigan to the east. The City of Chicago only recognizes a small portion of this region as Streeterville. Thus, it can be described as the Magnificent Mile plus all land east of it.

Streeterville includes some of Chicago's tallest skyscrapers, such as the John Hancock Center, and upscale stores, hotels, and restaurants. The east side of Streeterville is Navy Pier, the most visited attraction in Chicago, and the John Hancock Observatory, the eighth-most visited attraction in Chicago.

neighborhood_overview: This furnished apartment is located in the neighborhood of Lincoln Park. It is full of historic churches and brick row houses. Tree-lined residential areas give way to bustling businesses. Armitage Avenue is lined with independent boutiques and high-end retailers; Clark Street is packed with casual cafes, ethnic restaurants, and sweet shops. In addition to shopping and dining, Lincoln Park is a diverse art and entertainment destination. There is a plethora of museums, top theaters, and live music clubs to pick from. Also, there is plenty of natural beauty and outdoor scenery to enjoy. The neighborhood's namesake park is a sprawling 1,208 acres of green space with a zoo, nature museum, and conservatory. Head over to the lakefront beaches, where sand and surf are set against a backdrop of downtown skyscrapers. Being a 15 minute train ride from the Loop, Lincoln Park is a very close commute to the city’s primary business district.

description:
Our small home is at the intersection of the Woodlawn, Auburn Gresham & Grand Crossing neighborhoods on the South Side. A short 5 minute drive to the site of the Obama Presidential Library and Museum, 7 mins to the MSI, 12 mins to the University of Chicago, and 20 minutes to downtown, the home is situated on a quiet, safe block of mixed income families. The house has a 2 car parking pad in the back, a generous back yard and one small bedroom on the first level. Free street parking is plentiful.

The space
Our adorable home is compact (about 1170 Sq Ft.) On the first level, we have a living room, dining room, kitchen, half-bath, one small bedroom and washer/dryer. A flight of stairs to the second level, you will find the 3 other bedrooms, a full bathroom and an office/workspace which is connected to the 4th bedroom. Nice sized back yard with gazebo and deck, beautiful hydrangea garden as well as a 2 car parking pad. The home is on a peaceful, quiet block.
neighborhood_overview:
The home is located in an up and coming neighborhood on the South Side of Chicago which, while previously overlooked, is currently experiencing a strong uptick. The Obama Center, only a 5 minute drive from the property, will be sure to contribute to the already vigorous comeback of the area.

The much anticipated and lauded $100 Regal Mile Studios broke ground in February 2023 (slated to open Fall 2024) four blocks to the south of our home. The Regal Mile Studios project is a 380,000-square foot (7 acre) state-of-the-art media campus.

The block the home is located on is residential, quiet and safe with many working families who have long standing roots in the local community.

Supermarkets, banks (PNC), fast food and some retail are a short drive or walk from the home. The nearest decent restaurants are in Hyde Park, a 12 minute drive.

Downtown Chicago is about a 20-25 minute drive and public transport is within 5 min walking distance.

The dining scene is always buzzing, from authentic Italian food hall Eataly to high-end steakhouses like RPM Steak to the award-winning Pacific Standard Time. Good day, my name is Mr Phillips. I am a 54yr old(in February 2021) Command Master Chief, Persian Gulf war veteran and semiretired government law enforcement agent from the United States Department of Homeland Security.

I love reading and expanding my knowledge. I love a multitude of animé, comics and music. I am a gigantic music lover that loves listening to music from abroad and have a very extensive & multicultural music library. I definitely love to wrestle and have an overall good sparring match no matter how big, young, old or experienced my opponent is.

I am the type of person who thinks beyond outside the box. My thinking and mindset is on a whole other level, astral plane and dimension, so you can be laid back, comfortable and overall be yourself in my home without being in fear of being looked @ differently nor judged for being not "Normal" by other's standards. 

I'm not weird or normal, I am unique and magical unicorn wizard that poops rainbows, Lol. So yea, I believe you will feel comfortable in my home when I am present.

I am a very overprotective father and friend when it comes to the people I love and care deeply about. I'm a bit of a antisocial introvert, but strike up a conversation that interests my medulla oblongata and I can converse for hours. 

As you can tell, I love to be detailed and thorough and give as much information as possible instead of the usual "Bits & pieces" that people do nowadays.

I am extremely clean & organised. I can be a bit strict and rough around the edges, but I'm overall loyal, loving, kind hearted and a overall true person.

P.S. I love cats, Lol.

neighborhood_overview: This furnished apartment is located in South Loop. A dynamic neighborhood with a unique mix of attractions, shopping and history. Take a stroll along South Michigan Avenue and the nearby Prairie Avenue district to see "Millionaire's Row", an area lined with mansions belonging to Chicago's wealthiest elite. For shopping, visit the Roosevelt Collection, an open-air plaza, home to a cinema as well as premium local and national retailers. From day one, you’ll enjoy high-speed Wi-Fi, premium linens, and smart home entertainment. Plus, access to pools, gyms, and outdoor spaces in select buildings.

Why stress over your apartment? We provide a hassle-free alternative — a consistent, quality guest experience that starts even before you arrive. Because we let you book our most up-to-date apartment listings online, confirm with a click, pay securely, and check in easily. 

Even better? You can enhance your stay with car rentals, grocery delivery, laundry services, and more through our special partnerships. 

During your stay
Upon arrival, you’ll either be greeted personally by a Blueground team member or given self-check-in instructions. The entire apartment is yours! You’ll enjoy reliable support via email, phone, and our Guest App, where you can request everything from a home cleaning to extra towels. 

We’ll share all details upon confirmation of your stay.

neighborhood_overview:
Best amenity of the beach house is Rainbow Beach, easily one of our favorite beaches in Chicago. Just a 4 minute walk from our front door is this beautiful and quiet beach. Attached to the beach is Rainbow Beach Park, which has 2 playgrounds, basketball courts (adults and kids), nature preserves, and acres of lakefront walking paths.

Getting downtown is also easy with two Metra stops within 3 blocks which go directly to downtown, the famous Lakeshore Drive is 3 minutes away, and two major interstates are 7 to 10 minutes away.

There are two large, public golf courses along Lake Michigan less than 5 minutes as well. We are 10 minutes from the bustling and beautiful Hyde Park neighborhood, as well as the Museum of Science and Industry.

neighborhood_overview:
Chicago’s West Loop has earned a reputation as one of the most exciting areas to eat, drink, and experience the best of the city, so it’s no wonder locals are envious of anyone who gets to call this neighborhood home. Where industrial warehouses once stood, swanky high-rise apartments and condos now provide unbeatable views of the river and the city skyline. The central location puts you within walking distance of Downtown, Little Italy, and the Medical District, and the numerous bus and rail lines passing through make it easy to reach anywhere in the city.

The neighborhood is home to a truly mind-boggling selection of restaurants, bars, specialty grocery stores, art galleries, and performance venues of every shape, size, and description. The mix of modern and classical architecture combined with the various public art installations reflects the neighborhood’s unique historic and creative influences, and a distinctive European flair permeates the whole environment.

Much of its eastern edge is encompassed by the Museum Campus, an impressive collection of cultural treasures that includes the Field Museum, Adler Planetarium and Shedd Aquarium. This campus sits on scenic lakefront parklands that are an extension of Grant Park. With 319 acres of green space and recreational fields, Grant Park is known as "Chicago's front yard" to locals and also plays host to major city events such as Taste of Chicago, Chicago Blues Festival and Lollapalooza.

neighborhood_overview:
The Magnificent Mile encompasses the 13-block stretch of North Michigan Avenue that runs from the banks of the Chicago River to the south, to Oak Street to the north. The Magnificent Mile district extends a full square mile from North Michigan Avenue, including east to the scenic lakefront.

The Magnificent Mile is a spectacular showcase of style, flavor, entertainment and fun. With more than 460 stores, 275 restaurants, 60 hotels and unique entertainments and attractions packed and stacked along its length, The Magnificent Mile has an indulgence for every passion and every pocket.
host_about:
If you're looking to visit and stay in the Boston area, I would like to assure you my goal is to make your stay as comfortable, trouble-free and convenient as possible.

You will have the second floor, three-bedroom unit of my Somerville, Massachusetts home all too yourself. You'll be in a safe, historic neighborhood (Ten Hills), which is also home to  "Assembly Row", a brand-new, state of the art complex that provides the best of the best of food, shopping, movie theater, nightlife and entertainment in the Boston area.

Assembly Row is directly across the street from my home, and Downtown Boston, including the North End, Faneuil Hall, North Station, Beacon Hill, Back Bay, Fenway Park, the Boston Common, plus much, much more are less than 3 miles away, which is only a 7 to 10 minute ride, whether you are traveling by car or train. There is a dedicated train stop located at Assembly Row (Assembly Station), which is on the MBTA Orange Line.

The home is a spacious three-bedroom unit on the second-floor of the home (you will be the only one occupying it), which includes a living-room, dining-room, eat-in kitchen, master bedroom and bathroom. 

I provide all the amenities that I use and expect while I travel myself: cable television, high-speed internet, towels and complimentary beverages and bathroom cosmetics. 

If you should have any questions before your stay, please do not hesitate to reach out to me beforehand. As a local resident, I live within 5 minutes of the home. so if you should need anything else, I am only a phone call or text away!

Thank you and I look forward to making your stay enjoyable!
